:"https://lobste.rs/s/qqq4sd/thunderbird_littering_my_home"},{"short_id":"zsdjqm","created_at":"2026-06-08T10:50:25.000-05:00","title":"Scientists finally complete Schrödinger’s 100-year-old color theory","url":"https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/06/260606015140.htm","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"snej","user_is_author":false,"tags":["graphics","science"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/zsdjqm","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/zsdjqm/scientists_finally_complete"},{"short_id":"nwrobx","created_at":"2026-06-08T10:21:54.000-05:00","title":"Introduction to nixidy - Kubernetes GitOps with nix","url":"https://codedbearder.com/posts/nixidy-part-1-introduction/","score":8,"flags":0,"comment_count":7,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"granra","user_is_author":true,"tags":["devops","nix"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/nwrobx","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/nwrobx/introduction_nixidy_kubernetes_gitops"},{"short_id":"elvclc","created_at":"2026-06-08T10:20:53.000-05:00","title":"AstralOS: Audio, USB, NsCDE and more","url":"https://astral-os.org/posts/2026/05/31/audio_usb_nscde.html","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"mrunix","user_is_author":false,"tags":["osdev"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/elvclc","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/elvclc/astralos_audio_usb_nscde_more"},{"short_id":"qgy6ak","created_at":"2026-06-08T10:12:16.000-05:00","title":"Can we stop tagging every thing as vibecoding?","url":"","score":137,"flags":3,"comment_count":79,"description":"\u003cp\u003eAny article that even slightly mentions that AI exists is tagged as vibecoding, even when they have nothing to do with it. It:s getting out of hand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLE 1:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/ly0vif/my_students\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/ly0vif/my_students\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTagged as vibecoding, article contains a \u003cem\u003esingle\u003c/em\u003e passing reference\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ewhere people are racing to create intelligent machines, but only in order to make them slaves\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLE 2 (my own article; biased)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/vufbvv/user_doesn_t_care_you_should\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/vufbvv/user_doesn_t_care_you_should\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI quoted a \u003cem\u003eSINGLE\u003c/em\u003e example of someone putting an agentic spin on an old trope:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"Users don’t care whether the code was written by AI or by hand, or which framework you used. They care that the product works.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLE 3\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/gefcox/jolt_clojure_interpreter_on_janet\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/gefcox/jolt_clojure_interpreter_on_janet\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a code repo. There is no AGENTS.md, or CLAUDE.md, or any mention of AI in the readme...\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLE 4:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethis post, which someone will inevitably tag as \"vibecoding\"\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Any article that even slightly mentions that AI exists is tagged as vibecoding, even when they have nothing to do with it. It:s getting out of hand.\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE 1:\r\n\r\nhttps://lobste.rs/s/ly0vif/my_students\r\n\r\nTagged as vibecoding, article contains a *single* passing reference\r\n\r\n\u003e  where people are racing to create intelligent machines, but only in order to make them slaves\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE 2 (my own article; biased)\r\n\r\nhttps://lobste.rs/s/vufbvv/user_doesn_t_care_you_should\r\n\r\nI quoted a *SINGLE* example of someone putting an agentic spin on an old trope:\r\n\r\n\u003e \"Users don’t care whether the code was written by AI or by hand, or which framework you used. They care that the product works.\"\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE 3\r\n\r\nhttps://lobste.rs/s/gefcox/jolt_clojure_interpreter_on_janet\r\n\r\nThis is a code repo. There is no AGENTS.md, or CLAUDE.md, or any mention of AI in the readme...\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE 4:\r\n\r\nthis post, which someone will inevitably tag as \"vibecoding\"","submitter_user":"LAC-Tech","user_is_author":true,"tags":["meta","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qgy6ak","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qgy6ak/can_we_stop_tagging_every_thing_as"}]